Afrobeats act Segun Adekunle aka Labule has released his new single, Zero, today, Friday, January 28, 2022. Labule, in a statement, said Zero lacks fanfare, rather it is a score, a position, a digit that nobody wants to associate with just because of societal beliefs and negative perception towards it. According to him, not all bad or hopeless situations are really hopeless as the element of surprise is always lurking around to turn one’s hopelessness into optimism and victory.   Saheed Osupa urges Fuji stars to improve on lyrics     Gifted ranks top, enters season three     My entire acting career has been in Nollywood, Amata   Read Also: My entire acting career has been in Nollywood, Amata Labule said he decided to address this controversial digit, changing the narrative with the aim of inspiring and awakening his fans not to give up in the face of adversity this new year, in his new track titled Zero. - Advertisement - “We have unconsciously accepted and believe that the digit zero is synonymous with failure, emptiness. It is something we see in everyday life but, what you consider as empty, worthless can really work wonders with the element of surprise in it,” he said.